column29:
Battery negative line is seeing an overvoltage alarm on start up. 



!image-20240807-151804.png|width=1599,height=834,alt="image-20240807-151804.png"!

Battery voltage is driven up to rebus. possible hardware issue.
column167:
07/Aug/24 8:19 AM;712020:6db8ec7c-44cf-4e10-b192-736802f9538b;I used the danger commands to close connect fets on rebus and battery. I did a continuity check on REbus [-] to Battery [-] and REbus [+] to Battery [+]. If there was continuity that means a fet could be shorted. I had continuity between Rebus [-] and Battery [-] and some of the alarms I was seeing was overvoltage on BattNegative which supports the [-] line having a shorted fet.

We need to take this apart and check the BIP board, fets Q1,Q2 (Q1 and 2 are on [+] line but make sure not shorted), Q3, Q4, Q5 and Q6.
